sections.content:
Interpolation is the simplest form of data binding. You wrap any TypeScript expression in double curly braces {{ }} inside the template, and Angular evaluates it and renders the result as text.

You can use:
• Class properties: {{ title }}
• Method calls: {{ getFullName() }}
• Simple expressions: {{ price * 1.1 }}
• Ternary operators: {{ isLoggedIn ? 'Welcome!' : 'Please log in' }}

Angular automatically HTML-escapes the output, protecting you from XSS attacks. If you need to render raw HTML, use [innerHTML] with DomSanitizer.

